comment.body: This is difficult because there are many places where the code is modified from the pure Marlin code. Using the comparative method, I think I found most of the changes, and compilation based on 2.1.3 now starts correctly - except for one issue that I cannot locate yet. If I choose "FLASH EEPROM_EMULATION" (factory setting) I have to use the "save" command twice (no matter which parameter). If I select "SD_CARD_EMULATION" or "IIC_BL24CXX_EEPROM" (my printer has a physical eeprom added) the writing works correctly.

fix(conn/p2p): Gracefully handle invalid p2p address (#287)

* fix(conn/p2p): Gracefully handle invalid p2p address

Accerciser returns an empty string when `GetApplicationBusAddress`
is called on it.

The fix makes the problem known in debug and when tracing is set,
but stays silent otherwise as it isn't a big deal.

Also:

- fixes a new clippy lint where we must explicitly `.clone()`
a string instead of calling `to_string()` because it hides the
clone.

- fixes a handful of missing `# Example` tags / headers and
other minor brush-ups.

Make MatchType::Invalid default variant (#289)

Previously, the default MatchType variant was MatchType::All.

However, this does not interact nicely with the ObjectMatchRuleBuilder since this means even on properties which are not specified, the specified match type would still be MatchType::All.

What this meant in Odilia is that it would perform an "All" match on every preperty (which can sometimes cause an await point) even when the set of things to check was empty.

This fixes that issue, since the unspecified properties now get set to MatchType::Invalid (i.e.: do not perform search of this property). This has been updated in the documentation as well.

Replace async-std with smol (#291)

Since `async-std` is deprecated, we have replaced it, as recommended, with `smol`.

v0.28.0 release (#290)
